# Graendal · the hedonist who breaks minds

**Graendal** was once Kamarile Maradim Nindar, a renowned healer of the mind in the Age of Legends who secretly held her patients in contempt. As one of the Forsaken she surrounds herself with beautiful, enslaved thralls — kings, queens, and channelers reduced to ornaments by her Compulsion, kept for her pleasure and her use.

She is among the most insidious of the Forsaken precisely because she rarely fights in the open. She rules through others, weaving Compulsion to turn the powerful into adoring puppets who never know they have been taken, and she protects herself behind layers of misdirection. When at last her failures earn the Dark One's wrath, she is punished by being reborn into a deliberately ugly body — Hessalam, "without forgiveness."

Her nature is **ethereal** — her true weapon is not the spear or the sword but the unseen weave laid across another mind, the quiet rewriting of will. She fights in the medium of thought itself.

